What is an html element 
- an html element is defined by a start+tag, some content and an end tag/
" <()> " start tag
" </___> " end tag

"<TagName> Attributes
 stuff stuff
 </TagName>"
  
 # Block Elements
 - occupies a defined width,
 - starts on a new line
 - margin before and after
 example : <div>

 # Inline elements
 - occoupies an availble space only
 - their width is based on their content only
 Example: <span>

 
 Structure of html
 example code : 
 <html>
    <head>
    <title>Page Title </title>
    </head>
    <body>
        <h1>My first heading </h1>
        <p> My first paragrpah,,,, BLUSHESSSS </p>
    </body>
</html>

# HTML IS NOT CASE SENSITIVE

# ELEMENTS 
 - <p> : paragraph element
 - <hr /> : draws a horizontal line
 - <br /> : a new line

# inside my booty (<head></head>)
<meta name = "author" content=""/>
- specifies the author of a webpage

<meta name ="description" content=""/>
- short description of the page
- text often appears as a snippet in search engines


# Text Context
- Headings
    - 6 headings
    - size
- Paragraph
    - text under <p></p>
- Lists
    - two ways
        1. Ordered List 
        - uses <ol> 
        <li> </li>
        </ol>
        2. Unordered List
        <ul></ul>
        3. Definition Lists
        <dl></dl>
- Quotations
    - <quote></quote>
- Citations
    - <cite></cite>
- Images
    - <img>
    - <img src ="image link address"> 


- Aside - the element used to represent content that is INDERECTLY related
- HTML is the root element of an html document (wehh???)
- <link> tag will include the website icon on the browser tab
